      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THOR'S ANGEL (9) has missed by head in her las two, catching the eye last time in particular here. Building nicely and should be at her top now. Ready. KING OF THE TOWN (4) flashed home fresh into fourth, then was unlucky not to get the job done at the latest when nabbed on the line. Peaking now and is draws the A1 for Nottle. Big threat. ARIZONA SKY (3) left himself with too much to do fresh when turning over 5L off the leader but did pick up strongly in the run home to finish second. Is sure to have come on from that and is drawn much kinder this time. Bold showing anticipated. MIDNIGHT STAR (6) is racing well and has registered four minor placings in a row, last time out finishing third over 1800m at Ascot when she worked home in great style. Has a strong finish and now gets Pike on from a low draw. Watch for her bursting through. GOLD ENIGMA (8) is ticking along nicely and doesn't need to improve much to be fighting out the finish.",
